<title type="html"><![CDATA[Port SM2J to PAL?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7532&amp;p=74898#p74898"><![CDATA[
Yeah possible, but not easily.  I've always been outright impressed that the PAL version of SMB is sped up.  You almost have to code the game with that in mind from the beginning for it to be easy (or at least be smart about handling sprite movements and scrolling).  OTOH, for converting a PAL game to NTSC speed, it's not as hard to slow it down (the easy way is just skipping every 6th frame, which is what Nerdtracker 2 does - some stuff sounds slightly better in it's original PAL mode).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Mar 01, 2011 4:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
